HEADWORD: Cacuminal
<hw>Ca*cu"mi*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cacumen</ets>, <ets>cacuminis</ets>, the top, point.]</ety>
<fld>(Philol.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to the top of the palate; cerebral;
-- applied to certain consonants; <as>as, <ex>cacuminal</ex> (or
cerebral) letters</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cacuminate</ent>⟦br⟧
